Nigerian Singer cum songwriter, Sadiq Onifade better known as WurlD has announced that his forthcoming Extended Playlist (EP) titled ‘Afrosoul’ will be released on all digital platforms come May 15, 2020. The new EP is coming after the prolific singer released a new single titled ‘Ghost Town’ via platoon while a performance of the song originally debuted on a COLORS session on Thursday, April 30, following the release of his hit single “Love Nobody”. The EP will feature “Ghost Town” and “Love Nobody”; in addition to unreleased tracks “National Anthem (Growing Wings)”, “Story”, “Can’t Come Outside”, and more. The EP is available for pre-add It is however important to note that WurlD began his career writing for notable artists such as B.o.B., Trinidad James, Akon, Mario, and many more.